  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (63ed109 2022-08-09T00:12:23.543275Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nError:\r\n```\r\nFailed to resolve file: \"/pathToProject/myProject/src/interfaces/IConfig.sol\": No such file or directory (os error 2).\r\n Check configured remappings.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe path shown does not exist. I have a dependency at `/pathToProject/myProject/lib/myDepdendency/src/interfaces/IConfig.sol` which is imported and used within `myDependency` as `import \"src/interfaces/IConfig.sol\"`. \r\n\r\nIt seems the remapping isn't resolving that properly because both `myProject` and `myDependency` rely on imports using `src/` as an absolute path, and is resolving the dependency's `src/` to mean the root project's `src/`. (FWIW I also add remappings for the `test/` and `script/` dirs to use absolute paths for those too)",
